The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Raipur, Feb. 3 (PTI): Four American tourists and a local couple were allegedly assaulted and looted by some youths for alleged involvement in religious conversions.

 According to a complaint filed by a pastor, Harish Patel, the youths, who were raising Jai Sri Ram slogans, took away two laptops, cameras and cellphones from the foreigners, a police officer said. The attack took place last evening when a prayer meeting was on in a hall.

 New Delhi (PTI): A 12-year-old boy has been allegedly beaten up and tortured by a teacher and his wife in a Delhi madarsa. Faizal, a Noida resident, was denied food and forced to work as a domestic help by the teachers wife who locked him up for days, police said. A case was registered against the couple after a complaint by the boys father.

 Panaji (PTI): A man was killed and three others hospitalised when a swarm of bees attacked them in a village near Bicholim town, about 50 km from here.




